      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/b/3da27b/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-06-16T21:22:48.931Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hi - Ive had a few issues lately when following workouts in ERG Mode. Power seems to be spiking all over the place and is very hard to hold stable, even with a relatively steady cadence.</p>\n<p>I had an exercise the other day where I was trying to meet power at low cadence (about 55RPM), but just wasn\u2019t getting the resistance through the trainer to hit the power needed. The only way I could reach the power was to up cadence.</p>\n<p>All seemed to work fine a few weeks ago but the last few times I\u2019ve been having this issue.</p>\n<p>I\u2019ve started a workout using quick start &amp; seem to get fairly consistent power at high/low cadence when trying to hit target. But when I try and follow the structured workout, it seems to go back to spiking.</p>\n<p>I train with my partner at the same time using the same setup &amp; we\u2019ve both experienced this lately. (Side by side, following the same plan).</p>\n<p>We\u2019re each using a Kickr snap, paired to android via Bluetooth. (Pixel 9 &amp; 7 respectively).</p>\n<p>Couple of screenshots showing the issue - one showing pretty stable a few weeks back &amp; now the spiking/inconsistent power.</p>\n<p>Would appreciate any help available. Cheers.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/cc324d81ff58805269494b717d4325c7ea1a71c4.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/cc324d81ff58805269494b717d4325c7ea1a71c4\" title=\"Screenshot_20250616-222010~2\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/c/cc324d81ff58805269494b717d4325c7ea1a71c4_2_498x500.png\" alt=\"Screenshot_20250616-222010~2\" data-base62-sha1=\"t8paYXoe3gbCPHFOR4obgZ3uAkY\" width=\"498\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/c/cc324d81ff58805269494b717d4325c7ea1a71c4_2_498x500.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/c/cc32